HEADWORD: Morphotic
<hw>Mor*phot"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ fit for
forming.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Connected with, or becoming
an integral part of, a living unit or of the morphological framework;
<as>as, <ex>morphotic</ex>, or tissue, proteids</as>.</def>
